VIKOR ranks alternatives by balancing group utility (
S i
) and individual regret (
R i
) to find a compromise solution closest to the ideal [35], [36].

The Shannon Entropy method objectively determines criterion weights by measuring information variability (entropy) across alternatives. Criteria with higher variability (lower entropy) provide more discriminative information and receive higher weights (
w j
).

